Caption: ⚠️KUPACI KOSTIMI⚠️ Pođimo od pretpostavke da je ljeto. Svakih nekoliko godina se model kupaćih kostima mijenja i to je ok. Ove godine je IN onaj minijaturni donji dio kupaćeg koji imaš a nemaš, skroz ide u stražnjicu i ide visoko gore. Da. I to prekrasno stoji djevojkama (namjerno kažem djevojkama ne ženama) koje su vitke, bez celulita..Sad pođimo od pretpostavke da niiiiisu SVE žene (sad namjerno kažem žene jer kad dođeš u neke godine nikako ne možeš biti bez celulita, savršenog ravnog trbuha i jako slim, osim ako imaš neke suludo dobre gene sto je rijetkost), tako vitke, a u svim brandovima možeš kupit ili taj minijaturni u kojem bih osobno izgledala kao Milka koja je umjesto na ispašu zalutala na more, ili neki jednodjelni koji je, budimo realni, opet krojen za visoke vitke djevojke, i ne bih bila baš Milka al vrlo blizu…..Sad vas ja pitam. Šta je s ostatkom normalne populacije i normalnih ženskih tijela? Gdje su nestale normalne slip gaćice s vezanjem po strani ili bez vezanja? .Da se razumijemo. Meni je svako žensko tijelo lijepo, sa svim svojim manama, al se zaista osjetiš ‘kao da ne valjaš’ kad vidiš robu koja je krojena samo za visoke i vitke. .I da. CROP TOP! Pa za boga miloga zar stvarno mislite da svaka djevojka ili žena ima trbušnjake pa da si može dozvolit da to odjene s punim samopouzdanjem - a normalne majice bez da je običan t-shirt vise isto nema…. I tak… sjedim, pišem ovo i umirem od smijeha jer sam shvatila da ulazim u one godine kad mi sve smeta 😂 Al bez obzira na to, još uvijek nisam i neću bit visoka ni vitka 😂....
translate caption: ["⚠️BUYERS IN COSTUMES⚠️ Let's start from the assumption that it's summer. Every few years, the swimwear model changes and that's ok. This year, IN is that miniature bottom part of the swimsuit that you have and don't have, it goes all the way to the butt and goes high up. That. And it looks great on girls (I mean girls, not women) who are slim, without cellulite... Now let's start from the assumption that ALL women (now I say women on purpose, because when you get to a certain age, you can't possibly be without cellulite, a perfectly flat stomach and very slim, unless you have some insanely good genes, which is rare), so slim, and in all brands you can buy either that miniature one in which I would personally look like Milka who wandered off to the sea instead of grazing, or some one-piece that, let's be realistic , again tailored for tall slim girls, and I wouldn't be quite Milka, but very close....Now I ask you. What about the rest of the normal population and normal female bodies? Where have the normal side-tie or no-tie slip panties gone? .Let's understand each other. To me, every female body is beautiful, with all its flaws, but you really feel 'as if you don't fit in' when you see clothes that are tailored only for tall and slim women. .And yes. CROP TOP! Well, for God's sake, do you really think that every girl or woman has abs and can afford to wear them with full confidence - and there is no such thing as a normal t-shirt without being an ordinary t-shirt.... And so... I'm sitting, writing this and I'm dying of laughter because I realized that I'm entering those years when everything bothers me 😂 But regardless, I'm still not and I won't be tall or slim 😂...."]

Caption: 【巴士光年呈獻Busz Gallery城市畫廊 | Surrealhk X CircleDNA by Prenetics】 CircleDNA在7月迎接三週年！作品把超巨型CircleDNA Premium (全面基因測試) 坐立在東岸公園主題區，七彩繽紛的 「DNA雙螺旋結構」跨越維多利亞港，願與香港人邁進正向和美好的未來。同時體現 Prenetics 專業檢測服務的使命，旨於關注大眾健康需要，讓人們走進更健康的生活。如果想近距離睇呢幅作品12呎長巨大版本，快啲去下面展覽活動！「Busz Gallery城市畫廊」展覽日期：即日至2022年7月28日展覽地點：尖沙咀彌敦道柏麗購物大道地舖 60 號對外九巴巴士站展覽及有獎遊戲網頁：https://bus.asiaray.com/buszgallery2022
translate caption: ['【Bus Lightyear Presents Busz Gallery | Surrealhk X CircleDNA by Prenetics】 CircleDNA celebrates its third anniversary in July! The work sits the super giant CircleDNA Premium (comprehensive genetic test) in the theme area of \u200b\u200bEast Coast Park. The colorful "DNA double helix structure" spans Victoria Harbour, and is willing to step into a positive and bright future with Hong Kong people. At the same time, it reflects the mission of Prenetics\' professional testing services, which aims to pay attention to the health needs of the public and enable people to walk into a healthier life. If you want to see the 12-foot-long giant version of this work up close, go to the exhibition below! "Busz Gallery City Gallery" Exhibition Date: Now to July 28, 2022 Exhibition Venue: External KMB Bus Stop, 60 G/F, Park Lane, Nathan Road, Tsim Sha Tsui Website: https://bus.asiaray .com/buszgallery2022']

Bywa i tak, że z miejsc, które wywarły na nas wyjątkowe wrażenie, ślemy karteczkę do własnej skrzynki na listy. Gdy dociera chowamy ją do albumu ze zdjęciami. Tym razem z Włoch przywiozę jednak kartkę, która promowała muzealną wystawę archiwalnej fotografii największych gigantów w swoim fachu. Ponadczasowa w każdym calu, wyważona w ilości bieli i czerni, ujmująca.
translate caption: ['We send a postcard from every place we visit. The analog one, with a stamp with a stamp. So long chosen from among hundreds of ordinary people. We draw a few words, only a few, trying to contain the essence of experiences and impressions in them. Our tourist ritual that brings us a lot of joy. It also happens that from places that have made a special impression on us, we send a note to our own mailbox. When it arrives, we hide it in the photo album. This time, however, I will bring a card from Italy, which promoted a museum exhibition of archival photographs of the greatest giants in their profession. Timeless in every detail, balanced in the amount of black and white, endearing.']

Caption: Am heutigen  gibt's nach all dem Krabbelgetier mal ein Katzenschnäuzchen.Das ist die Schnauze meines Ex-Katers Loki. Ex-Kater? Ja, nach einem kleinen Unfall hielten wir es für besser, wenn er umzieht.Lange Geschichte kurz erzählt: an Weihnachten, genau der 24., kam meine Mutter mit ihrem Hund zu Besuch. Loki ist eigentlich ein friedlicher Kerl, daher wollten wir sehen, ob es den Abend klappt. Nun kam sie aber etwas früher und der Kater war noch im Haus. Ich blieb also bei ihm. Als er den Hund sah, begann er zu knurren und ich nahm ihn auf den Arm (doofer Fehler). Dann hustete (weil Havaneser nicht bellen können) der Hund und Loki drehte durch. Er kannte weder Freund noch Feind und bevor er meine Große erwischt, wollte ich ihn rausschmeißen. Er verbiss sich in meine Hand und durchlöcherte sie an 21 Stellen. Da man mit Katzenbissen nicht spaßen soll, bin ich sofort in die Notaufnahme - im Glauben nach kurzer Wundversorgung zur Bescherung wieder zu Hause zu sein. NOPE. Ich lag um 21 Uhr im OP. Nächsten Tag hatte ich trotz sofortigem Antibiotika eine Blutvergiftung. Meine Hand wurde wegen der Infektion in einer Woche 3 Mal operiert. So lange blieb ich auch im Krankenhaus.Das Gute: An meinem Entlassungstag kam meine Frau auf die Geburtenstation und entgegen der Coronavorschriften durfte ich dann, da ich direkt von der Station kam, wie bei einer normalen Geburt als Partner von Beginn an dabei sein.Da wir uns dann aber unsicher waren wegen dem Säugling und gesehen hatten, wie schnell die Sache dramatisch wird, zog Loki zu meiner Schwester, wo er mit 3 weiteren Artgenossen heute ein sehr glückliches Leben hat. Seht selbst:  Aber was lehrt uns das? Fasst einen durchdrehenden Kater nicht an und falls doch, spaßt nicht mit Katzenbissen. Es kann lebensgefährlich sein. Trotzdem liebe ich noch Tiere. Und wenn die Kinder größer sind, ist ein Haustier definitiv nicht ausgeschlossen. Mit Loki hatte ich mich danach schnell wieder vertragen.
translate caption: ["Today, after all the crawling things, there's a cat's snout. That's the snout of my ex-cat Loki. ex-hangover? Yes, after a small accident we thought it would be better if he moved. Long story short: on Christmas, exactly the 24th, my mother came to visit with her dog. Loki is actually a peaceful guy, so we wanted to see if it worked out tonight. But now she came a little earlier and the cat was still in the house. So I stayed with him. When he saw the dog he started to growl and I picked him up (stupid mistake). Then (because Havanese can't bark) the dog coughed and Loki went nuts. He knew neither friend nor foe and before he caught my big one, I wanted to kick him out. He bit my hand and punctured it in 21 places. Since you shouldn't joke with cat bites, I immediately went to the emergency room - believing that after a short treatment of the wound I would be home for presents. NOPE. I was in the OR at 9 p.m. The next day, despite immediate antibiotics, I had blood poisoning. My hand had 3 surgeries in one week for the infection. That's how long I stayed in the hospital. The good thing: On the day I was discharged, my wife came to the maternity ward and contrary to the corona regulations, since I came directly from the ward, I was allowed to be there as a partner from the beginning, just like in a normal birth. There but then we were unsure about the baby and had seen how quickly things would become dramatic, Loki moved to my sister, where he now has a very happy life with 3 other conspecifics. See for yourself: But what does this teach us? Don't touch a crazed hangover, and if you do, don't joke around with cat bites. It can be life threatening. However, I still love animals. And when the kids are bigger, a pet is definitely not out of the question. I quickly got along with Loki again after that."]

Caption: "The principal planning strategy of the new building was to create a household from a hierarchy of rooms with different amenities placed around a shared common space with multiple purposes, behind a common front door. This created a household with a sense of belonging to the common space and a greater sense of personal responsibility to it and encourages students out of their rooms and into the common space. It also meant a household could be vertically composed of students with various university experiences, creating small communities with a social structure more aligned with the indigenous idea of Kinship.Central to the building’s cultural understanding is the creation of the Banksia form, an open four-storey structure centrally located at the confluence of the building and campus networks, veiled in expanded mesh and green vegetation, and creating a counterpoint to the rigidity of the more institutional adjacent buildings. On the ground and first floor, the Banksia is a bleacher seat forum, the second level is the central external social learning and reflection space, and the top is an externally open but shrouded cultural ceremony space with a fire and smoking pit. The dominant form imposes itself on the College creating a significant landmark that reinforces the cultural importance of the facility.": Wilson Architects  : Douglas Mark Black

Caption: Like the state of Alabama has two kinds of music, country and western, it seems we have two kinds of wrens. The Bewicks and the Carolina. Carolina Wrens are more reddish-brown above and pale cinnamon below whereas Bewick's Wrens are browner above and grayish below. Their ranges overlap only in a limited part of the central U.S.Carolina Wrens are largely resident, and will only disperse beyond their range after mild winters. Permanent breeding locations range from eastern Nebraska, southern Michigan, southeast Ontario and the New England states to Mexican states such as Coahuila, Nuevo León, San Luis Potosí and Tamaulipas and the Gulf Coast of the United States.Bewicks Wrens are now extremely rare east of the Mississippi River. It is still found along the Pacific Coast from Baja California to British Columbia, in Mexico, and in a significant portion of the Southwest, including Texas, Arizona, New Mexico, and Oklahoma.Post includes combo video 1, bewicks Wren and range 2,3 and Carolina Wren and range 4 and 5

Caption: Stoked!  This is one of my favorite pics of the year, and an amazing experience. I'll be making a whole video about photographing these guys and conservation efforts to rebuild their population.I was really careful to not disturb these birds, and l just laid down on the beach and allowed the birds to act normally, which included walking towards me.  This one is only a few days old.  I'm not as close as I appear though, this was shot at 700mm and cropped.  Given this is a sensitive species, I won't be revealing a detailed location.Piping Plover (In French, Pluvier siffleur).

Caption: Birbirinden farklı üç çocuğun hikayesini konu alan ve Mucize’nin devamı niteliğinde sayılan bu kitabı okumanızı öneririm. İçinizi ısıtacak ve yüzünüzde gülümseme bırakacak olan bu kitap aynı zamanda bize madalyonun öteki tarafından bakmanın önemini de göstermektedir. ⭐️“Mucize ve Ben üç farklı bakış açısıyla Auggie’nin dünyasına yepyeni bir pencere açarak okuldan önceki hayatı ile beşinci sınıfta yaşadıklarının bilinmeyen yönlerine ışık tutuyor. Okurlar bu kez zorba Julian, Auggie’nin en eski dostu Christopher ve okuldaki yeni arkadaşı Charlotte’ın gözünden tek ortak noktaları olan Auggie’yi görecek. Bu üç mucizevi hikâye, sıradışı yüze sahip sıradan çocuktan ayrılmak istemeyenler için hazine niteliğinde.”
translate caption: ["I recommend you to read this book, which is about the story of three different children and is considered a sequel to Miracle. This book, which will warm your heart and leave a smile on your face, also shows us the importance of looking at the other side of the coin. ⭐️“Miracle and Ben, from three different perspectives, opens a brand new window to Auggie's world and sheds light on the unknown aspects of his life before school and what he went through in fifth grade. This time, readers will see Auggie, the only thing they have in common, through the eyes of the bully Julian, Auggie's oldest friend Christopher and his new friend at school, Charlotte. These three miraculous stories are treasures for those who want to stay away from the ordinary boy with the extraordinary face.”"]
